{
  "texts": [
    "Various benchmarks have been proposed to assess how well LLMs can follow instructions across different contexts and complexities, using powerful LLMs as judges (Zheng et al., 2023; Dubois et al., 2024) or verifiable rubrics as metrics (Zhou et al., 2023; He et al., 2024).",
    "While current frontier LLMs demonstrate strong performance on many instruction-following tasks, challenges remain, particularly in handling complex, multiturn instructions or instructions that require reasoning over long contexts (He et al., 2024; Deshpande et al., 2025), which motivates our work to further explore and address these limitations through rubric-based training and evaluation.",
    "Our proposed benchmark, AdvancedIF, is mostly related to MultiChallenge (Deshpande et al., 2025), which aims to evaluate LLMs' multi-turn IF capabilities with instance-level rubrics.",
    "However, our benchmark provides a more holistic evaluation covering broader scopes (Table 2 and Section A) and features pure expert-written prompts and rubrics for more realistic and aligned evaluation.",
    "Reinforcement Learning with Human Feedback."
  ]
}